race.comment: PUGLIA (10) resumes. She's been a bit costly in six starts to date, beaten when in the market but it's largely been in strong maidens and she's run well every time she's stepped out. Drawn low, she'll land on speed and can get the job done. BAYWATCH (17) was well supported on debut at Pakenham last time in, battling home to finish sixth and sent for a spell thereafter. 1400m should suit her much better and she can be a quick improver this time in. JOIN THE QUE (3) has been thereabouts in two runs to date, coming through a strong maiden at Geelong last time. He can continue to improve. RED FEATHERS (12) is fresh off a short break and has the ability to be running well on best figures.
